+# Technical Details: Compute Test Utilities and Grouper Tests Refactoring
+
+## Architecture Overview
+
+### Test Utility Organization
+
+```
+arrow/compute/
+├── kernels/
+│   ├── test_util.h         # Shared kernel test utilities
+│   └── test_util.cc        # (existing, ~370 lines)
+└── row/
+    ├── test_util.h         # NEW: Row-specific test utilities
+    ├── grouper_test.cc     # ENHANCED: 2 → 21 tests
+    ├── grouper.h           # Public API
+    └── grouper.cc          # Implementation
+```
+
+## New Test Utility Functions
+
+### 1. ExecBatch Creation
+
+```cpp
+inline ExecBatch MakeExecBatch(const std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Array>>& arrays)
+```
+- Converts vector of arrays to ExecBatch
+- Handles empty input
+- Consistent length validation
+
+```cpp
+inline ExecBatch ExecBatchFromJSON(
+    const std::vector<std::shared_ptr<DataType>>& types,
+    const std::vector<std::string>& json_strings)
+```
+- Creates ExecBatch from JSON representation
+- Type-safe array construction
+- Simplifies test data creation
+
+### 2. Validation Utilities
+
+```cpp
+inline void ValidateGroupIds(const Datum& group_ids, int64_t expected_length,
+                             uint32_t max_group_id)
+```
+- Verifies group ID array is valid UInt32Array
+- Checks all IDs are within valid range
+- Ensures no null values in group IDs
+
+```cpp
+inline void ValidateSegment(const Segment& segment, int64_t expected_offset,
+                           int64_t expected_length, bool expected_is_open,
+                           bool expected_extends)
+```
+- Validates segment properties
+- Checks offset, length, is_open, and extends flags
+- Used in RowSegmenter tests
+
+```cpp
+inline void ValidateSegmentsCoverBatch(const std::vector<Segment>& segments,
+                                      int64_t batch_length)
+```
+- Ensures segments are contiguous
+- Verifies no gaps or overlaps
+- Confirms segments cover entire batch
+
+### 3. Test Data Generation
+
+```cpp
+inline ExecBatch GenerateRandomBatch(
+    random::RandomArrayGenerator& rng,
+    const std::vector<std::shared_ptr<DataType>>& types,
+    int64_t length, double null_probability = 0.1)
+```
+- Creates random test data
+- Supports multiple data types
+- Configurable null probability
+
+## Test Coverage Analysis
+
+### Grouper API Coverage
+
+| Method | Test Count | Coverage |
+|--------|-----------|----------|
+| `Make()` | 15 | Constructor with various types |
+| `Consume()` | 13 | Basic, sliced, multi-batch |
+| `GetUniques()` | 3 | Single/multi-key, empty |
+| `Reset()` | 1 | State reset verification |
+| `num_groups()` | 13 | Throughout tests |
+| `MakeGroupings()` | 1 | Static method |
+| `ApplyGroupings()` | 1 | Static method |
+
+### RowSegmenter API Coverage
+
+| Method | Test Count | Coverage |
+|--------|-----------|----------|
+| `Make()` | 6 | Various configurations |
+| `GetSegments()` | 6 | Different key patterns |
+| `Reset()` | 1 | State reset |
+| `key_types()` | Implicit | Throughout tests |
+
+### Data Type Coverage
+
+The `VariousTypes` test validates grouping across 13 data types:
+
+1. **Integers**: int8, int16, int32, int64, uint8, uint16, uint32, uint64
+2. **Floats**: float32, float64
+3. **Boolean**: boolean
+4. **Strings**: utf8, large_utf8
+5. **Binary**: binary, large_binary
+
+## Test Design Patterns
+
+### Pattern 1: Basic Functionality
+```cpp
+TEST(Grouper, SingleKeyInt32) {
+  auto array = ArrayFromJSON(int32(), "[1, 2, 1, 3, 2, 1, 3, 3]");
+  ExecBatch batch = MakeExecBatch({array});
+  ExecSpan span(batch);
+
+  ASSERT_OK_AND_ASSIGN(auto grouper, Grouper::Make(span.GetTypes()));
